My App Platform — Setup Reference
Server & Infrastructure

Home server running Ubuntu, username pip
Docker managed via Portainer
Nginx Proxy Manager (NPM) for reverse proxying, container name nginx-proxy-manager
All app containers must join the nginxproxymanager_default Docker network
NPM data lives at /home/pip/docker/npm/data/

Domain & DNS

Domain: schaffner.xyz managed at Hostpoint
Dynamic IP handled by DuckDNS: schaffnerxyz.duckdns.org
Each new app gets its own subdomain CNAME in Hostpoint: appname.schaffner.xyz → schaffnerxyz.duckdns.org
SSL certificates via Let's Encrypt through NPM (request after DNS propagates, ~5 min)
Wildcard A/AAAA records are locked by Hostpoint, so each subdomain needs its own explicit CNAME

App Files Location

All apps live under /opt/phisch_apps/ on the server
Each app has its own folder: /opt/phisch_apps/appname/
Apps are deployed by SSH-ing in and running docker compose up -d from the app folder
Portainer is used to monitor/restart containers but not to deploy (file mounts require deploying from the server directly)

App Structure (Static Tier)
Each static app folder contains:
/opt/phisch_apps/appname/
  index.html
  css/
  js/
  docker-compose.yml
  app.json
docker-compose.yml template:
yamlversion: "3.9"
services:
  appname:
    image: nginx:alpine
    container_name: appname
    restart: unless-stopped
    volumes:
      - ./:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro
    networks:
      - nginxproxymanager_default
networks:
  nginxproxymanager_default:
    external: true
app.json template:
json{
  "name": "App Display Name",
  "description": "One sentence description.",
  "icon": "🔧",
  "route": "https://appname.schaffner.xyz",
  "tags": ["KWI"],
  "tier": "static"
}
Dashboard

Lives at https://apps.schaffner.xyz
Container name: phisch_apps-dashboard
Config at /opt/phisch_apps/dashboard/apps.json
Adding a new app = add an entry to apps.json + restart dashboard container:

bashcd /opt/phisch_apps/dashboard && docker compose restart
NPM — Known Gotcha
NPM has a bug where saving a proxy host while simultaneously requesting an SSL cert can silently fail (no .conf file gets written to /home/pip/docker/npm/data/nginx/proxy_host/). Always:

Create the proxy host without SSL first → verify the .conf file appears
Then edit it to add the SSL certificate separately

Checklist for Each New App

 Create folder /opt/phisch_apps/appname/
 Add index.html, assets, docker-compose.yml, app.json
 Use curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/... to download files (never save via browser)
 docker compose up -d from the app folder
 Add CNAME appname.schaffner.xyz → schaffnerxyz.duckdns.org in Hostpoint
 Wait ~5 min for DNS propagation (nslookup appname.schaffner.xyz)
 NPM: create proxy host (no SSL) → confirm .conf file exists → add SSL cert
 Add entry to dashboard/apps.json with full https:// route → restart dashboard
 Test in incognito window (avoid browser cache issues)

